body:
File: compiler/bytecode-graph-builder.cc
Key visitors and helpers:
- void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitLdaLookupSlot() { BuildLdaLookupSlot(TypeofMode::kNotInside); }
- void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitLdaLookupSlotInsideTypeof() { BuildLdaLookupSlot(TypeofMode::kInside); }
- void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitStaLookupSlot() { ... selects Runtime::kStoreLookupSlot_{Strict,SloppyHoisting,Sloppy} based on flags; binds accumulator with result }
- void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitPushContext() { Node* new_context = env->LookupAccumulator(); env->BindRegister(reg0, env->Context()); env->SetContext(new_context); }
- void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitPopContext() { Node* context = env->LookupRegister(reg0); env->SetContext(context); }
- void BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitCreateWithContext() { Node* object = env->LookupRegister(reg0); ScopeInfoRef scope_info = const idx1; const Operator* op = javascript()->CreateWithContext(scope_info); Node* context = NewNode(op, object); env->BindAccumulator(context); }
- BuildLdaLookupSlot(TypeofMode): emits CallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadLookupSlot or kLoadLookupSlotInsideTypeof) and attaches frame state.
- BuildLdaLookupContextSlot(ContextKind kind, TypeofMode): performs CheckContextExtensions(depth) to fast-path context/global slot loads via LoadContext/LoadScriptContext or LoadGlobal; slow-path merges to runtime LoadLookupSlot/InsideTypeof; sets marks for eager checkpoint.
- BuildLdaLookupGlobalSlot(TypeofMode): similar to context version, fast path LoadGlobal with feedback, slow path CallRuntime LoadLookupSlot/InsideTypeof.
- Context extension checks & helpers:
  * Environment* CheckContextExtensions(uint32_t depth): consults TryGetScopeInfo() and broker empty-context-extension dependency to possibly emit dynamic checks via CheckContextExtensionAtDepth; returns slow env merging branches when extension present.
  * Environment* CheckContextExtensionsSlowPath(uint32_t depth): builds JSHasContextExtension(d) branches and calls CheckContextExtensionAtDepth to test extension slot != undefined.
  * OptionalScopeInfoRef TryGetScopeInfo(): attempts to recover scope info from current context node (create context ops, parameter, etc). Used to replace dynamic checks with compilation dependencies when possible.
  * Environment* CheckContextExtensionAtDepth(Environment* slow_env, uint32_t depth): emits LoadContext(depth, EXTENSION_INDEX,false), ReferenceEqual to Undefined; branches to merge slow path when extension exists.
- VisitToObject present as VisitToObject() { BuildCastOperator(javascript()->ToObject()); }
- Additional feedback for globals in BuildLoadGlobal and VisitLdaGlobal/InsideTypeof use javascript()->LoadGlobal(name, feedback, typeof_mode) and feedback_vector_node().
